I was so excited to spend a magical evening @QueensMuseum for their 2023 Annual Gala! Queens Museum is dedicated to presenting arts and educational programming for the people of New York, and particularly the residents of Queens, a uniquely diverse ethnic, cultural, and international community. The gala honored Angelo Baque (@angelobaque) and Sable Elyse Smith (@sable_elyse) with a beautiful musical performance by Nick Hakim (@en_hakim). 
 
Thank you, Queens Museum President and Executive Director Sally Tallant, Chief Operating Officer Debra Wimpfheimer, and Board Chair Peter Warwick for welcoming me to this incredible celebration highlighting the vibrance and diversity of Queens.

Visit queensmuseum.org for current exhibitions, including the ongoing exhibition “Glori Tuitt 
Black, Trans, & Alive (Qweens Song).”

The @statenislandmuseum strives to spark curiosity and generate meaningful shared experiences through natural science, art, and history, and I was thrilled to attend their gala honoring Marie H. Cole and Lucille Herring. 

As a new resident of Staten Island, attending this event was especially meaningful to me. I’m so proud to support Staten Island Museum and its work providing an environment and education programming that is truly welcoming and inclusive of all people. Thank you, President and CEO Janice Monger and Board Chair Daniel Jost, for welcoming me to this event. 

Visit statenislandmuseum.org for exhibitions and programs. Don’t miss “Vulnerable Landscapes,” an exhibition highlighting local individuals advocating for climate justice and a deeper connection to where we live.

📸: Bill Higgins

“It was all a dream” is an understatement. To celebrate Brooklyn’s own Biggie Smalls in partnership with the Universal Hip Hop Museum @uhhmuseum with Lil’ Cease @lilcease DJ Red Alert @kooldjredalert Ralph McDaniels @videomusicbox Papoose @papoose and so many Hip Hop legends was a night for the history books. I was honored to reunite with Biggie’s children CJ @cjordanwallace and T’yanna Wallace @tyanna810 for this incredible tribute to their father. 
You KNOW we had to do it up for Biggie. I was thrilled to celebrate the life of Christopher Wallace @christopherwallaceway @edgenyc @hudsonyards highest outdoor sky deck in the Western Hemisphere, alongside the Universal Hip Hop Museum @uhhmuseum 

This celebration came as a part of Hip Hop 50, as we celebrate the legacy and impact of hip hop across the world. 

So thrilled to celebrate Biggie and hip hop. Learn more about the Universal Hip Hop Museum at uhhm.org.

#biggiesmalls #nyculture #uhhmuseum #lilcease #djredalert #ralphmcdaniels #papoose #biggie #edgenyc #hudsonyards #nyc #hiphop #music

I was so excited to attend the Brooklyn Music School’s @bmsbrooklyn Gala at Rule of Thirds !!! This year, BMS celebrates 114 years of providing communities with accessible, globally influenced performing arts programming to students of all ages, socio-economic backgrounds, abilities, and professional aspirations. The theme of this year’s gala, “Accessing the Arts,” builds on the organization’s mission of “Arts for All,” highlighting the importance of accessibility in the performing arts space. BMS presently provides high-quality performing arts instruction to 800 students on-site, an additional 1,500 through its outreach program all around the city, and to roughly 8,000 indirect audiences each year.

For more information, please visit their website at
https://www.brooklynmusicschool.org/gala-2023

It’s Sailing Season! ⚓ 

I had the pleasure to join Captain Jonathan Boulware, Manhattan Borough President Mark Levine, and local leaders at the South Street Seaport Museum to announce the opening day of the 2023 Sailing Season of the Museum’s historic vessels, the Pioneer and W.O. Decker.
 
“@SeaportMuseum is dedicated to preserving New York’s history as a great port city, and it houses an extensive collection of art and artifacts, a maritime reference library, exhibition galleries and education spaces, historic vessels, and more! Aboard the Pioneer and the W.O. Decker, the Museum welcomes the public to embark on unforgettable journeys viewing NYC’s most iconic landmarks through a one-of-a-kind sailing experience. We are proud to support the South Street Seaport Museum and its programming!” 
- @nyculture 

Visit southstreetseaportmuseum.org to learn more.

📸: Richard Mitchell

It’s my favorite time of the year, BAM Dance Africa!!! These are some of my favorite Dance Africa moments from the last ten years. Get your tickets now! @bam_brooklyn 
This Memorial Day weekend, the vibrant artistry and revolutionary history of Ghana inspires an immersive, electrifying celebration of dance. Now in its 46th year, DanceAfrica presents a choreographic and musical journey through the past and present of Ghanaian culture, connecting ancestral traditions to contemporary achievements on the BAM stage. Featuring performances by the National Theater of Ghana’s National Dance Company, the DanceAfrica Spirit Walkers, Arkestra Africa with Musical Director K. Osei Williams featuring Afropop vocalist Amma Whatt and BAM Restoration Dance Youth Ensemble, this year’s tribute to Ghanaian excellence promises to entertain, educate, and empower.

BAM Dance Africa is the ultimate Brooklyn Family reunion! I love everything about it... from reuniting with friends and family to the incredible dance experiences inside and outside of the Opera house to the African cuisine to the shopping... did I say shopping... did I say shopping. You know I lose my mind and my bank account every year. But it feels so good to get one of a kind pieces by Black owned artisans. Congratulations BAM on an incredible Dance Africa celebrating the culture and history of Ghana. 

#BAM #bamdanceafrica #ghana #brooklyn #nyculture #culture #fashion #nycfashion

Amongst blossoming flowers 🌺 and lush greenery, I had a FANTASTIC time celebrating @nybg at their Conservatory Ball. The New York Botanical Garden is a cultural gem that is dedicated to showcasing the diversity of the plant world through gardens, exhibitions, and education programs.

This year’s Ball celebrated NYBG's new summer exhibition by Ebony G. Patterson, who is the first artist to be embedded within the institution for an immersive residency. Congratulations to Ebony on her amazing exhibition titled "…things come to thrive…in the shedding…in the molting…," which evokes the natural world and creates a platform for conversation about larger societal issues.

Thank you, NYBG CEO and President Jennifer Bernstein and Board Chair J. Barclay Collins II, for welcoming me to celebrate NYBG!

🌱 Visit nybg.org to check out Ebony G. Patterson’s incredible exhibition, on view at NYBG through September 17, 2023, and other programs!

Photos by Darian DiCianno/BFA.com

Echoes of Tradition and Diversity Resonate at Drums Along the Hudson: A Melodic Tapestry of Pow Wow Dances, Music, Food, and Art, Embracing NYC’s Native American and Multicultural Vibrancy! What an amazing experience!

Happy Birthday, Biggie!!! 🥳 What a joy to return to St. James Place, now formally named Christopher Wallace Way, to celebrate Biggie where he grew up in Brooklyn!

Music and the arts have a special way of bringing communities together and it was awesome to see everyone come out to celebrate Biggie’s legacy at this amazing block party celebrating what would have been his 51st birthday.

#hiphop #biggiesmalls #brooklyn

Great to be featured on @toddwhartonofficial NYC’s Independent Talk Show to speak about Biggie’s legacy at @edgenyc 

FaceTimewithToddWharton.com
bookings@facetimewithtoddwharton.com

Guess who was selected to be the QUEEN of this year’s Mermaid Parade @mermaidparade in Coney Island @coneyislandfun ? ME!! ME!!! ME!!!!! Oh, I’m so excited!!!! So excited!!!! Join me and Mermaids everywhere on Saturday, June 17th at 1pm in Brooklyn’s own Coney Island for all of the royal festivities. I will be channeling my inner Halle Bailey @hallebailey in honor of her role as Ariel in the Little Mermaid while celebrating HipHop’s 50th Anniversary @hiphop50 ! Don’t miss it and bring the whole family. You won’t want to miss my Royal Costume!!!

What an honor to be the Queen of the 40th Annual Mermaid Parade! 

Since 1983 the Coney Island Mermaid Parade has been a cultural hit and consistently is one of Brooklyn’s biggest attractions, bringing in upwards of 830,000 attendees!
The creativity, talent, diversity, and unity of @mermaidparade is what helps make NYC so special!
“I want the little girl in me and the little girls just like me who are watching to know that they’re special, and that they should be a princess in every single way!” - Halle Bailey

Happy Father’s Day to all the Amazing Father’s in my life! Thank you for loving me and supporting me and being there in the good times and challenging times. Father’s are so necessary in our lives!

Bobby Digi! You are an incredible Father to your four sons and to the entire community! You exemplify fatherhood each and every day, and as Prince would say, “Today is your day Daddy to do whatever you want.”

Dance is part of NYC’s DNA, and I was thrilled to celebrate @thejoycetheater , one of our city’s most important dance institutions, at their gala this year. 

I would like to give a huge congratulations to Joyce Board Chair Emerita Virginia A. Millhiser and Executive Director Linda Shelton, who has led this theater for an incredible 30 years, and who we celebrated this evening. 

Generations of artists have performed at The Joyce, and audiences know that there is no place like it in the world when it comes to joyful, exciting, remarkable dance programming.

The Joyce Theater is now presenting “SW!NG OUT,” a New York Times’ Critic’s Pick, which celebrates the unbridled joy of Lindy Hop, through July 2! Learn more by visiting joyce.org.

YES!!!! Today, I was the keynote speaker at Laurie A. Cumbo Enrichment Center Graduation for UPK3 and UPK4 Students. What an incredible honor to speak at the school named in your honor. This incredible school is a world-class, state-of-the-art educational center with a waitlist already after one year of its opening. It is filled with love and designed for academic success with the arts centered at everything they do! I am feeling so proud that I was able to share this day with my Mom! Special shout out to my former Chief of Staff Tasha Young, who worked with me for four years to save this school from being demolished!

The Laurie A. Cumbo Enrichment Center is located at  180 Myrtle Avenue 
Brooklyn, New York 11201

For more information, visit:
https://wearebcs.org/what-we-do/education-and-youth-development/

#bcs #fortgreene #laurieacumboenrichmentcenter #UPK4 #UPK3 #spelman

Please join me in wishing the man, the myth, the legend @bobbydigi_sinyc the happiest of Birthdays!!! I hope you enjoyed The surprise morning Birthday Party organized by the Prince! Wishing you many more Happy Birthdays and beautiful days ahead!!!

I was honored to speak at Mayor Eric Adams’ Juneteenth Celebration at Gracie Mansion and the Flag Raising Ceremony at Bowling Green. There were so many incredible celebrations all across New York City and it was such a great reminder of how far we have come while also recomitting ourselves to the continuous fight for freedom and equity. I applaud those hard-working individuals who had the vision and persevered and never gave up on their goal to make Juneteenth a Federal Holiday. Ashe

#Juneteenth #freedom #graciemansion #juneteenthflagraising

🔥 From stilt walkers to steelpan drums to fire eaters and folklore, @tropicalfete Caribbean Carnival Festival was FANTASTIC! Held at the Central Library Branch of the Brooklyn Library, the event was an explosion of diverse Caribbean cultures. I’d like to congratulate Averi Harper, ABC News Deputy Political Director, for being crowned as the carnival queen. 
 
Tropicalfete is dedicated to connecting communities through Caribbean culture with visual arts, fashion, music, dance, theater, film, and new media. At the event, the organization launched a new limbo app which was designed by students in their computer production program, who combined STEM with culture for the project. 

✨Visit tropicalfete.org to learn more about upcoming events. 
📲 Download “Tropicalfete’s Limbo” app from Google Play and the Apple Store.

Please join us in wishing our Prince a very Happy 6th Birthday!!! Wow! Where did the time go? We are so blessed to experience this journey called life with Prince. We can't believe you will be starting 1st grade next month! Mommy and Daddy love you so much!

So happy to join Rosanna Scotto, the host of Good Day New York to celebrate @HIPHOP50! So many incredible events happening this weekend. See you at @yankeestadium tonight and hope to see you at all of the block parties this weekend at www.5x5blockparty.com
All I can say is that Hip Hop was at Gracie Mansion today in all of its spectacularness! Who would have thought Hip Hop would take it this far. The ancestors are pleased!  #hiphop #hiphop50

What a night! So proud to be at the opening of the @mocada_museum Ubuntu Garden! It has been an honor to have the torch passed to MoCADA's Executive Director @missaimstar who continues to take the Museum to the next level. It was so great to see so many old friends and made some new ones along the way. So happy that MoCADA owns this space. #mocada #ubuntu #feelingproud

OMG! So many great moments from the 5x5 Block Party celebrations in all five Boroughs! What an incredible weekend celebrating the 50th Anniversary of Hip-Hop! It felt like the New York I grew up in! It was beautiful. My favorite part was celebrating this weekend with Prince!

I've always wanted to go to India but I figured since I can't get to India right now, then I will bring India to Times Square!!!! What an amazing honor to join the Consul General of India in New York (@indiainnewyork) and the Indo American Arts Council (@iaac.us) today to unveil the INCREDIBLE Chakra Sculpture in Times Square in recognition of India’s 77th Independence Day!! Enormous thanks to Indian Consul General, Randhir Jaiswal and IAAC Board Members Anil Bansal and Rajeev Kaul for having me. And shout out to chef Vikas Khanna and dancers Rimili Roy and Surati for providing powerful reminders of the beauty and strength of Indian culture! 

The Chakra Sculpture is a symbol of India’s rich cultural heritage and values. This sculpture in Times Square stands 8 feet tall and weighs an astonishing 4,000 pounds!! While surrounded by the hustle and bustle of New York, this is a replica of the Konark Chakra, a revered emblem from the 13th century Sun Temple in Konark, Odisha, where it is one of 24 intricately carved wheels adorning the temple. The magnificent carvings and representation of the Konark Chakra continue to captivate viewers, a testament to India's architectural and cultural legacy.

In New York, our diversity is our strength, and I'm proud to stand alongside our Indian neighbors on behalf of @NYCMayor and @NYCulture to celebrate this momentous day. The Chakra Sculpture exhibit will be open to the public from August 15 to August 22. Check it out in Times Square Plaza between 44th and 45th Streets. Don't miss this remarkable installation!!!

The best part of the 56th Annual West Indian American Day Labor Day Parade is the reunion with friends that have become family. So many good times! And nobody likes to take pictures more than me on this festive day! Thank you @sesameflyersinternational and @rickdavyfwbk for making the look all possible!

Come on down to the Queens County Fair!!! 

This year marks the 40th anniversary of @queensfarm's fabulous festival of farming, food, fun, and FREE mac and cheese!! (You read that right). The fair is also home to NYC's ONLY corn maze - better known as the Amazing Maize Maze - this year inspired by the shape of a 1954 Ford tractor. It's by far the most enjoyable way to get lost anywhere in the five boroughs!! 

There's truly something for everyone here. Concerts, performances, a STEAM activity center from @lewislatimerhouse, historic tours, arts programming, and so much more. The Queens County Fair continues Saturday and Sunday, September 9-10, 11 a.m. to 6 p.m. Learn more at queensfarm.org. See you there!!!!

♥️ NYC is so happy to get back some LOVE!! ♥️

What an honor to join The @RobertIndiana Legacy Initiative and @RockefellerCenter today to welcome this iconic public artwork back to NYC with a vibrant new coat of paint. Along with the LOVE sculpture, Rockefeller Center is hosting two other installations by Indiana: the monumental ONE Through ZERO (The Ten Numbers) (1980-2001) - enormous metal sculptures of numerals - while the 193 flags surrounding The Rink at Rockefeller Center will feature images from Indiana’s Peace Paintings series, created as a response to the 9/11 attacks, which he witnessed while in New York City.

In a space like Rockefeller Center, artwork needs to make big, bold gestures to hold its own, and Indiana's works does so beautifully. Public art is essential to what makes NYC so vibrant and full of energy, and there's no better stage for it than right here in the heart of NYC, where Indiana's powerful messages of unity, acceptance, and love resonate with everyone who encounters these amazing works. 

Check them out now through October 23. More info at www.rockefellercenter.com. ♥️

I was honored to join @nycmayor Eric Adams and Reverend Al Sharpton (@real_sharpton) at the @africanburialground for an unveiling of the Congressman John. A. Lewis (1940 – 2020) US Forever Postage Stamp. I can remember growing up and being excited to see the Mary McLeod Bethune, Harriet Tubman, and Sojourner Truth African American Heritage Stamps—there’s just something so powerful about being able to see ourselves being honored for our accomplishments. It solidifies the progress that we’ve made. And for those like Congressman John A. Lewis, it means the marches he led and the work he did fighting for what he knew was right, has now been honored. 

While I served on City Council, I had the pleasure of meeting John A. Lewis at the Central branch of the Brooklyn Public Library. He was unbelievably kind and passionate, and I’m thrilled to have been able to shake his hand. 

I thank the African Bural Ground, U.S. National Park Service, and The Black Women's Leadership Caucus for hosting this wonderful event. I have to give a shout out to poet Najaya Royal, a young poet who read for my inauguration at City Council—a full circle moment to see her recite poetry in honor of Congressman John A. Lewis.

As I think of the African Burial Ground, a memorial for over 15,000 unnamed enslaved Black people, and honoring Congressman John A. Williams on those grounds, it is a powerful reminder of how far we have come and how we must continue the struggle for equality. Now. head on down to the post office and get your Congress Member John Lewis Postage Stamps like it was a Biggie Smalls MetroCard.

This Sunday, October 22nd, 2023, join me to recognize the 24th anniversary of the SOARING, monumental "Triumph of the Human Spirit," created by the visionary Dr. Lorenzo Pace to honor our African ancestors in Foley Square! This important day of remembrence is curated by Jamel Gaines @creativeoutletdance of Brooklyn. This monumental piece is just across from the African Burial Ground,  the oldest and largest known excavated burial ground in North America for both free and enslaved Africans. Dr. Pace's work - commissioned through @NYCulture's Percent for Art program in 1993 -  is in direct conversation with this sacred space, a five-story, 300-ton, black-granite sculpture that dominates the civic heart of NYC. Please share with your community and bring our children so that they will know the history that they stand upon! 

#africanburialground #creativeoutletdancetheaterofbrooklyn #creativeoutlet #triumphofthehumanspirit

I know I’m not supposed to pick favorites, but @materialsforthearts gala was truly 🔥🔥🔥. I just had to put on my sparkling jumpsuit to show up and show out for their #MaskedMarvelous gala!! ✨

With bumping beats from the DJ, stilt walkers, cheerleaders, sword swallowers, roving tango dancers, tarot readers, and a makeup bar – they went all out to celebrate the vibrancy of the arts in New York City! 

MFTA is a program of @NYCulture with support from its nonprofit partner Friends of Materials for the Arts. It is our city’s largest creative reuse center dedicated to supporting arts and culture. MFTA operates a 35,000-square-foot warehouse of supplies in Long Island City, Queens, which are provided, free of charge, to arts organizations, public schools, and City agencies across the five boroughs. 

I have to give a HUGE shout out to MFTA Executive Director Tara Sansone! Whether it’s addressing the COVID pandemic or making sure asylum seekers are served in New York City, MFTA does it all! And at the same time Tara and her team make sure that our teachers and artists get the supplies they need – and that 1.5 million pounds of materials are distributed throughout New York City each year! 

Congratulations to the fabulous @MachineDazzle, who gave a sneak peek for his gallery show opening at MFTA in November. And congratulations to the evening’s honorees Public Artist in Residence (#PAIRnyc) @Modesto_Flako_Jimenez, @Bloomberg LP Head of Corporate Philanthropy Nancy Cutler, and @PentagamDesign Partner Luke Hayman for their work with MFTA. 

I also had a fantastic time dancing the night away with former @NYCulture Commissioner @gonzalocasals! Shout out to you, Gonzalo!! 

Thank you for all you do for our city, MFTA!!!

#Repost @nyculture

🎃 Important message from Minion / Cultural Affairs Commissioner Laurie Cumbo: spooky season has arrived in the city that never sleeps, and it's going to be epic! In addition to @StatenIslandZoo's annual #Spooktactular celebration (where Minion Cumbo filmed this greeting and which wrapped last weekend), we’re sharing just a few of the #Halloween events (with a cultural bent) happening across the five boroughs:

1. @SnugHarborCCBG – Join one of Staten Island’s most beautiful historic destinations—and if the legends are true, one of the most haunted—for a Spooky Snug Harbor tour on Sunday, October 29 and Tuesday, October 31.

2. @NYSCI - Get ready for a pawsome time at Dogs! A Costume Parade, where our furry friends strut their stuff in adorable costumes on Saturday, October 28 from 11am to 12pm.

3. @SocratesPark – Socrates Sculpture Park’s annual Halloween Harvest Festival is back with a pumpkin carving contest and a costume making workshop with @NYCulture’s very own @MaterialsfortheArts on Saturday, October 28 from 12pm to 5pm.

4. @BAM_Brooklyn – Enjoy BAM’s festive Halloween party, BAMboo!, with arts and crafts and carnival games on Tuesday, October 31 from 4pm to 7pm.

5. @BKCM – Don’t miss spine-chilling musical performances, a haunted instrument garden, and of course candy at Brooklyn Conservatory of Music’s annual Halloween party on Tuesday, October 31 from 4pm to 6pm.

6. @BronxZoo – Oh my gourd-ness! Check out Bronx Zoo’s Pumpkin Nights featuring live pumpkin carving, treats, and games now through October 29 from 6pm to 10pm.

7. @NYCParks – Come to St. James Park in the Bronx for an afternoon of family games, sports, fall crafts, and more on Saturday, October28 from 12pm to 5pm.

8. @NuyoricanPoetsCafe – Enjoy a Halloween Salsa Jam at Nuyorican Poets Café on Sunday, October 29 from 7pm to 10pm. Catch this event at the Nuyorican before they close for an exciting renovation project (which the Department of Cultural Affairs is proud to support)!

9. @NYCHalloween – From Canal Street to 16th Street, NYC’s annual Village Halloween Parade will celebrate its 50th anniversary on Tuesday, October 31 from 7pm to 11pm.

#NYCulture #NYC #Get
Proudly serving the cultural community of New York City as Commissioner of @NYCulture. Working with @NYCMayor to #GetStuffDone for all New Yorkers.
